InfraSec Roadmap (Zero to Hero)
│
├── 1. Fundamentals of Networking and Security
│   ├── TCP/IP Model
│   ├── DNS, DHCP, IP Addressing
│   ├── VPN, SSL/TLS, Firewalls
│   └── Zero Trust Architecture
│
├── 2. Operating System Security
│   ├── Linux Security
│   │   ├── SSH, Firewall Configuration (UFW, IPTables)
│   │   └── File Permissions and Auditing
│   ├── Windows Security
│   │   ├── Active Directory Security
│   │   └── PowerShell Scripting for Security Automation
│
├── 3. Cloud Infrastructure Security
│   ├── AWS
│   │   ├── EC2 Security
│   │   ├── S3 Bucket Security
│   │   ├── IAM (Identity and Access Management)
│   │   └── AWS Shield and WAF
│   ├── Azure
│   │   ├── VM Security
│   │   └── Azure Security Center
│   └── GCP (Google Cloud Platform)
│       ├── GKE Security
│       └── Google Cloud IAM
│
├── 4. Network Security
│   ├── Firewalls and IDS/IPS
│   │   ├── Tools: pfSense, Snort, Suricata
│   ├── Network Segmentation
│   ├── VPN and Remote Access Security
│   └── Intrusion Detection Systems (IDS)
│
├── 5. Virtualization and Container Security
│   ├── Virtual Machines (VM) Security
│   ├── Docker Security
│   │   ├── Docker Bench
│   │   └── Seccomp, AppArmor, SELinux for Containers
│   └── Kubernetes Security (K8s)
│       ├── Pod Security Policies (PSPs)
│       ├── Network Policies
│       └── Tools: Falco, Kube-bench
│
├── 6. Identity and Access Management (IAM)
│   ├── Active Directory Security
│   ├── Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)
│   ├── SSO (Single Sign-On) Integration
│   └── Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
│
├── 7. Patch and Configuration Management
│   ├── Automating Patches (Ansible, Puppet, Chef)
│   └── Secure Configurations (CIS Benchmarks)
│
├── 8. Incident Response and Disaster Recovery
│   ├── Incident Response Plan (IRP)
│   ├── Forensic Investigation (Network, Disk)
│   ├── Data Backup and Recovery
│   └── Disaster Recovery Drills
│
├── 9. Security Monitoring and Logging
│   ├── SIEM Tools
│   │   ├── Splunk
│   │   ├── ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
│   │   └── Graylog
│   └── Continuous Monitoring (Nagios, Zabbix)
│
└── 10. Soft Skills and Communication
    ├── Collaborating with IT Teams
    ├── Documentation of Security Policies
    └── Communication in Incident Response
